name: Reading Lights
directions: Second floor by left stairs to the right
comment: You're not necessarily have to be a customer/visitor just don't act like you're too much in a rush. cool people.

name: Barraco's
directions: Right when you walk in, there is a family bathroom near the Hostess stand.
comment: You might have to be a paying customer, but I'm sure if you asked to use the restroom they would not mind.

name: Meijers-Sussex
directions: Front restroom area between the service desk and Ben's pretzels
comment: Has a baby changing table inside

name: Starbucks
comment: Only one unisex bathroom since this is a small location.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Back right corner, right next to the demo station.
comment: Good, queer friendly staff. As an ex-employee I can say it's one of the most lgbt friendly trader Joe's locations on the island :)

name: Southern Sweets Bakery
directions: To the left as you enter shop
comment: Accessible to everyone

name: The Wine Seller/The Patio
directions:
Access through The Wine Seller: go to the back of the restaurant and through a door. Walk down a long hallway until you reach two gender neutral bathrooms.
Access through The Patio: use the door opposite the entrance to the patio
comment: You can access the bathroom through The Patio's patio without buying anything. If you would feel more comfortable buying something, go by a water/soda from The Patio and ask about restrooms. The Wine Seller is an upscale restaurant, so its probably not a good idea to go there unless you plan on staying for a drink or food.

name: Smokey Mountain Coffee Roasters
comment: It is a coffee shop, so you should probably buy something to use the restroom. A small cup of coffee is about $1.50 if you are concerned about spending money.

name: Boynton Health Services, University of Minnesota
directions: 2nd floor, turn right, then it's the second hallway on the right.
comment: Fragrance-free, but a little cramped for an accessible restroom.

name: The Keweenaw Co-op
directions: Up the stairs, first door on right.
comment: not handicap accessible (not sure what accessible referred to) because the building is super old

name: Dylans candy bar
directions: Third floor by the cafe gender neutral bathrooms with candy wallpaper!! Also harry potter candy!
comment: It was really nice cause theres just one bathroom with two locking stalls and a communal place to wash hands.

name: Starbucks
comment: Anyone gives you an issue, let a barista know. Discrimination is not tolerated here.

name: Exploratorium
directions: right as you get into the museum past the ticketing desk. There are both gendered bathrooms and two unisex restrooms.

name: Dobbs Ferry Library
directions: The ones by the entrance are single gendered though also single stall and lockable, but if you go upstairs there's a gender neutral one right across from the elevator.

name: Racked Up-Cycled Fashion Boutique
directions: In the back past the dressing rooms

name: Westwood Collegiate
directions: Second floor, tucked away from the hallway, by the back of the school.
comment: You probably wont be allowed to enter the school just to use the restroom.

name: Summit Coffee
directions: In the back of the coffee shop. You can also enter through the back door if you find that more comfortable.

name: Spielbound Board Game Cafe
directions: To the left as you walk in the door, through the library down a little hall. Two single room all gender restrooms.
comment: Someone will greet  you or ask if you're going to be playing games, say you're here to check out the game library since you've never been in before and wanted to see what it's all about. When you leave wave or say thank you

name: Target
directions: Directly left of front door

name: 35 E Elizabeth Ave (Office Building)
directions: Second floor
comment: Two gendered single bathrooms. Building has various professional tenants (doctors, etc) and no receptionist/visible security personnel. Back entrance with large parking lot.

name: Starbucks
directions: In back of store, two gender neutral single stalls.
comment: Probably preferred to be paying customer, but not that important.

name: Liverpool Guild of Students
directions: Ground floor by the Sphinx bar.

name: Hot Pink Cake Stand
directions: In back end of storefront.
comment: The store has a sign up saying that their bathrooms are intended to be gender inclusive.

name: Movie tavern denton
directions: 2 private restrooms across from the typical restrooms.

name: The Public Theater
directions: Enter into the main lobby and follow the signs towards the back left corner
comment: The building is fully open to the public after 2PM daily. Large restrooms, one with private stalls and the other with private stalls and public urinals, have the following signs posted outside: "Gender diversity is welcomed here; please us the restroom that best fits your gender identity or expression. To access gender neutral restrooms, please ask a staff member for assistance."

name: Bluestockings Bookstore and Cafe
comment: The store itself is wheelchair accessible but the restroom is not. Restroom is open to anyone who needs it.

name: Princess Anne Library
directions: walk in and go straight back to your right. it's in the junior book section.

name: Leon Johnson Hall
directions: 6th floor by East Stairs

name: Tealuxe
comment: You must grab the goblet with the bathroom key on it before entering and while it would be polite to buy something you are not required to.

name: Amsterdam University College
directions: All restrooms on the second floor

name: Walgreens
directions: Through the door underneath the exit sign on the wall far left of the front door, then turn left.

name: Wendy's
directions: To the right of the counter, straight back. The right side doors let you breeze past without talking to anyone.
comment: I personally know, as of June 2016, two nonbinary people work here, and no one will judge you for which bathroom you use.

name: Wendy's
directions: Just to the right of the cash register, right-side door let's you breeze past without looking at anyone, straight back.
comment: As of right now there are at least two NB people working there, one DMAB and one DFAB, and no one who works there will judge you for which you go into.

name: Primo Pizza
directions: Go left when entering it is in the back corner past the mirror.
comment: You can just walk in no one cares whether you buy anything or not.

name: In-Tea
directions: Down the hallway in the back of the store, on your left, restroom is marked
comment:
You have to be a paying customer.
May be accessible, but I'm not sure

name: Hansen-Willis Hall
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms on the first floor - right right after the front desk and they're on the left.
comment: If you don't live in the building, the front desk will let you in if you knock on the door. You may be able to catch someone coming in or out too.

name: Lunder Arts Center
directions: To the left immediately in the main atrium
comment: open 9-5

name: Union Square
directions: First floor near side doors

name: Upright Citizens Brigade Theater, East Village
directions: Two single-stall bathrooms in the lobby. ~Four~ single-stall bathrooms in the basement.
comment: Very progressive, cool comedy theater in the East Village. No judgement, guaranteed safe space

name: Bertucci's
directions: Back of the restaurant, past the kitchen.
comment: Possibly act like you're meeting someone at a table?

name: Museum of Science and Industry
directions: On the lower level in the hallway between the food court and the farm tech exhibit there are four single stall family restrooms. One to either side of each gendered restroom.
comment: Around lunch time there's usually a line made up of parents who don't feel comfortable taking their small children who are gendered differently then they are into the gendered restrooms with them.

name: Mischief toy store
directions: First floor, all the way back and to your right. There is also one upstairs if you want more privacy
comment: If you need anything let the staff know. They will help you.

name: Bounty Kitchen
directions: I

name: The Roundhouse
directions: Upstairs, there are male and female restrooms, and a gender neutral toilet also.
comment: Of course, I believe you have to be attending an event at the Roundhouse to use the bathroom.

name: University of Connecticut, Austin Building
directions: First floor, if you enter from the front go down the small set of stairs, go through the door to the hallway, then turn left at the end. There should be a sign telling you which door to go through on the left. There is another hallway, turn right, and it's on the left.
comment: You can enter the building even if you're not a student

name: Cochrane HIgh School
directions: Across from the Woman's and Men's washrooms
comment: It is in a school building, keep this in mind if you need to use it.

name: University of Strathclyde
directions: 6th floor

name: Burial Grounds
directions: restrooms straight in the back hallway, one off to either side
comment: you don't need a key; if they're locked, they're occupied. also i'm saying they're not accessible because they have doorknobs. other than that they're on the ground floor, wide doors, standard size hallway, possibly handrails inside the bathrooms themselves

name: Starbucks
directions: Upstairs in the centre, it's on your right when you go into the Starbucks, the code is 4321
comment: You might have to buy something, I'm not sure on the policy, but that might just be to get the bathroom code, which is 4321, so I'd try and go in before making a purchase

name: Starbucks
directions: Two unisex singles are located in the back of the cafe, past the first exit sign on the right.
comment: No need to buy anything, if the door is locked it's just occupied.

name: Herron School of Art and Design IUPUi
directions: Two stalls located across from the administration office, on the first floor. Two more stalls located next to the print making shop on the first floor
comment: I'd guess 50% of the school is LGBTQ+ and at least 98% is LGBTQ+ friendly, don't be afrail to ask for help or directions

name: IUPUI Taylor Hall
directions: Two single stalls located on first floor main hallway. One is next to the Mens room and the other is across from the African American student organization office

name: Brigantia Building
directions: Go past the reception desk, down the passage on the right.
comment: University building - need to be a student.

name: Half Price Books - Rice Village
directions: To the back and left
comment: 2 single-stall unisex restrooms in the store

name: New square cafe
comment:
Gendered door signs, but single stall, ungendered once in stall.

"female" is shared with accessible room.

Customers only I think.

name: Newcastle City Library, 33 New Bridge St W, Newcastle upon Tyne, Tyne and Wear NE1 8AX, UK
directions: Childrens' and IP floor
comment: Part of the 'Use Our Loos' scheme, so no patronage needed

name: Keele University SU
directions: Up one flight of stairs

name: Starbucks
directions: Right of the counter
comment: Have to have bought a drink/be with somebody who has (I think)

name: Starbucks
directions: Right of the counter
comment: Have to have bought a drink/be with somebody who has (I think)

name: The Pompeii Lounge
directions: Not sure about the first floor restaurant but the upper levels are apartments renovated into a lounge/bar, and all the bathrooms are single stall, unisex. Not very accessible due to them being on upper levels but if you can get up, they are spacious. Also, whenever I've gone in, they ID'd everyone at the door
comment: I think you have to be a paying customer, but if you go in when it's open and go upstairs like you're meeting someone, you could use the restroom with ease.

name: UCN
comment: It is a university, but if you just walk in and look like you belong there, no one should question it. There are gender neutral restrooms all around campus, some of which are handicap accessible.

name: UCN
comment: It is a university, but if you just walk in and look like you belong there, no one should question it. There are gender neutral restrooms all around campus, some of which are handicap accessible.

name: Gigantium
directions: Opposite from the swimming hall are gender neutral restrooms

name: Aalborg Universitetshospital - Psykiatrien
directions: go through indgang 1, and then turn to the left and on the left side you will see gender neutral bathrooms

name: CTYS
directions: On third floor near the waiting room entrance, but anybody can use it!
comment: It is only open when the building is open, the main building door is locked at 6.

name: Lee 1 Clemson university
directions: Right in front of girls bathroom next to lee 1 gallery

name: Walmart
directions: By the layaway desk in the back of the store, between electronics and shoes

name: Tart
directions: It's a little bit out of view, but it's closer to the door than the paying counter and on the right side
comment: It's pretty roomy (not exactly sure how accessible), single stall, and I believe it has a changing table.

name: Tipton City Aquatic Center
directions: Directly left of the front desk, not easy to miss.
comment: It's usually used for changing but there's also a toilet. It's probably supposed for pool-goers but idk if they'd really try to stop you if you tried just to use it quickly without swimming. I'm just letting people know that this is a place they can change/whatever if they don't feel they fit into the boy/girl "categories".

name: Maverick
directions: In the back left of the store. Door is on the right-hand side of the hallway.
comment: Just make sure you knock first! Some of the locals (especially people who drink and stop in at night) forget to lock the door. Don't want to end up in an embarrassing situation.

name: Wegmans
directions: One family stall in the cafe side of the store. Bathrooms at the cash registers are handicap accessible but gendered and multi stall.
comment: You don't have to be a customer. Cafe side restrooms are generally quieter because it's a lower traffic area.

name: Sizzle Pie
directions: Ask for key at front counter, staff is friendly and accepting from experience.
comment: Usually must be customer but food is cheap.

name: Kepler's Books
directions: At the end of the cash register by the front entrance.
comment: Public single-stall restroom in very LGBT+ friendly store. You do NOT need to be a customer to use it.

name: Tory Row
directions: Straight back through the dining room/bar.
comment: I think you have to be a customer but nobody said anything to me when I went before we sat down. If it's busy they probably won't notice you, it can get a bit crowded. The people working here at the time (Thursday evening) seemed young and very nice/accepting.

name: Republic Cafe & Bistro
comment: They're both marked "WC" for "water closet", not a gender.

name: Petco
directions: Left side of store, in the far back in a short hallway. If you see blue double doors you're on the wrong side.
comment: If marked restroom is full, the room just past it in the hallway is also a restroom even though it is marked as employees only. Most employees will have no problem with you using it if you ask first.

name: Fusian
directions: Back of the store
comment: Usually you have to be a customer but if it's busy no one will care

name: Woolley Market
directions: Up the stairs, turn right, straight ahead.
comment: Small local grocery and deli/cafe, you don't have to be a paying customer, but it would probably be best to browse a little bit before using the restroom.

name: Yochi
directions: Walk straight through till the back of the shop, on the left hand side after the Yogurt dispensers
comment: Do not have to be a paying customer :)

name: Mr Green Bubble
directions: In the back
comment: Not sure whether or not you have to be a paying customer

name: Zebra Tattoo and Body Piercing
directions: In the back
comment: Probably try to act like you are browsing but the people working there are really nice about it.

name: Score on Davie
directions: Very back of store, gendered doors both lead to the same washroom
comment: 19+ Bar

name: Shawano Lake County Park
directions: Enter the park and go straight through the 4 way intersection. Go over the hill and down into the loop to park. The unisex bathroom is on the south end of the pavilion by the beach, facing the lake.
comment: The park is open until 10 pm. After that you're not *technically* supposed to be on the park grounds, but this is not heavily enforced, and simply using the bathroom would certainly not be an issue. If you come on a busy day (hot weekend day, usually), the unisex bathrooms are harder to get a hold of because they are usually used as family changing rooms. Because of this, there may be lines, which could be problematic if you're trying to avoid looks or small children saying something inopportune.

name: Target
directions: By the front entrance next to the customer service desks.
comment: There are gendered restrooms but there is also a single stall gender neutral handicap bathroom next to them that anyone can use.

name: Kinkead's
directions: In the back

name: Tea Haus - Northcross Mall/Plaza
directions: Next to a Wich Which. If facing Walmart, it's on your left.
comment: If it's busy you can just walk to the back. If it's quiet, maybe grab something on the way out? The staff is pretty friendly, so it might be ok to just dash in and out.

name: Rose Library (East Campus Library)
directions: Two separate single bathrooms in the 24-hour room.
comment: You need to have a valid JMU JACard to access the 24-hour room.

name: Benedict - Mezes Hallway, University of Texas
directions: Between the two buildings in the lowest hallway there's a restroom. Use the entrance behind the flowers instead of the main doors. It's next to the auditorium and next to a vending machine area.

name: Carrier Library
directions: Third floor, in the back left-hand corner

name: Southern Oregon Humane Society
directions: To the right once you go in the main door
comment: It is an animal shelter but they're very nice and most of the staff that I know of are LGBT+ friendly.

name: Flo Paris Bakery & Cafe
directions: The plaza connected to James Coney Island. In the corner. The restrooms are in the back.
comment: If it's busy, they probably won't notice,  if it's quiet, maybe purchase a croissant to be less conspicuous?

name: FIT Japanese Store
directions: Inside the Chinatown Plaza next to Bambu (faces away from the street)
comment: Pretend to browse for a bit. The restrooms are in the back. Hard to miss.
